Installing Yii via command-line:

(example installation instructions)
cd ~
wget http://yii.googlecode.com/files/yii-1.1.10.r3566.tar.gz
tar -zxvf yii-1.1.10.r3566.tar.gz
rm yii-1.1.10.r3566.tar.gz
cp yii-1.1.10.r3566 yii
cd /var/www/lightswitch
~/yii/framework/yiic webapp .

Notes: these instructions are for the version of Yii that was available at the time of writing. 
Check on the Yii website (http://www.yiiframework.com) for the latest version of Yii and replace the address and filename as necessary.

The above will install the Yii framework into your home directory (~).

You can then access the basic application via http://<ip_of_this_machine>/lightswitch

